{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My name is Kate Hartman."},{"time":7000,"text":"And I like to make devices"},{"time":9000,"text":"that play with the ways"},{"time":11000,"text":"that we relate and communicate."},{"time":13000,"text":"So I'm specifically interested in how we, as humans,"},{"time":16000,"text":"relate to ourselves, each other"},{"time":18000,"text":"and the world around us."},{"time":28000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":32000,"text":"So just to give you a bit of context,"},{"time":34000,"text":"as June said, I'm an artist, a technologist and an educator."},{"time":37000,"text":"I teach courses in physical computing"},{"time":39000,"text":"and wearable electronics."},{"time":41000,"text":"And much of what I do is either wearable"},{"time":43000,"text":"or somehow related to the human form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46000,"text":"And so anytime I talk about what I do,"},{"time":48000,"text":"I like to just quickly address"},{"time":50000,"text":"the reason why bodies matter."},{"time":52000,"text":"And it's pretty simple."},{"time":55000,"text":"Everybody's got one -- all of you."},{"time":57000,"text":"I can guarantee, everyone in this room,"},{"time":59000,"text":"all of you over there, the people in the cushy seats,"},{"time":61000,"text":"the people up top with the laptops --"},{"time":63000,"text":"we all have bodies."},{"time":65000,"text":"Don't be ashamed."},{"time":67000,"text":"It's something that we have in common"},{"time":69000,"text":"and they act as our primary interfaces for the world."},{"time":72000,"text":"And so when working as an interaction designer,"},{"time":75000,"text":"or as an artist who deals with participation --"},{"time":77000,"text":"creating things that live on, in or around the human form --"},{"time":81000,"text":"it's really a powerful space to work within."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"So within my own work,"},{"time":86000,"text":"I use a broad range of materials and tools."},{"time":89000,"text":"So I communicate through everything from radio transceivers"},{"time":92000,"text":"to funnels and plastic tubing."},{"time":94000,"text":"And to tell you a bit about the things that I make,"},{"time":96000,"text":"the easiest place to start the story"},{"time":98000,"text":"is with a hat."},{"time":101000,"text":"And so it all started several years ago,"},{"time":103000,"text":"late one night when I was sitting on the subway, riding home,"},{"time":106000,"text":"and I was thinking."},{"time":108000,"text":"And I tend to be a person who thinks too much and talks too little."},{"time":111000,"text":"And so I was thinking about how it might be great"},{"time":113000,"text":"if I could just take all these noises --"},{"time":115000,"text":"like all these sounds of my thoughts in my head --"},{"time":117000,"text":"if I could just physically extricate them"},{"time":119000,"text":"and pull them out in such a form"},{"time":121000,"text":"that I could share them with somebody else."},{"time":124000,"text":"And so I went home, and I made a prototype of this hat."},{"time":127000,"text":"And I called it the Muttering Hat,"},{"time":129000,"text":"because it emitted these muttering noises"},{"time":132000,"text":"that were kind of tethered to you,"},{"time":134000,"text":"but you could detach them"},{"time":136000,"text":"and share them with somebody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"So I make other hats as well."},{"time":147000,"text":"This one is called the Talk to Yourself Hat."},{"time":149000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":151000,"text":"It's fairly self-explanatory."},{"time":153000,"text":"It physically carves out conversation space for one."},{"time":157000,"text":"And when you speak out loud,"},{"time":159000,"text":"the sound of your voice is actually channeled back into your own ears."},{"time":165000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":167000,"text":"And so when I make these things,"},{"time":169000,"text":"it's really not so much about the object itself,"},{"time":172000,"text":"but rather the negative space around the object."},{"time":175000,"text":"So what happens when a person puts this thing on?"},{"time":178000,"text":"What kind of an experience do they have?"},{"time":180000,"text":"And how are they transformed by wearing it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"So many of these devices"},{"time":188000,"text":"really kind of focus on the ways in which we relate to ourselves."},{"time":191000,"text":"So this particular device is called the Gut Listener."},{"time":194000,"text":"And it is a tool"},{"time":196000,"text":"that actually enables one"},{"time":198000,"text":"to listen to their own innards."},{"time":201000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":208000,"text":"And so some of these things"},{"time":211000,"text":"are actually more geared toward expression and communication."},{"time":213000,"text":"And so the Inflatable Heart"},{"time":215000,"text":"is an external organ"},{"time":217000,"text":"that can be used by the wearer to express themselves."},{"time":220000,"text":"So they can actually inflate it and deflate it"},{"time":223000,"text":"according to their emotions."},{"time":225000,"text":"So they can express everything from admiration and lust"},{"time":228000,"text":"to anxiety and angst."},{"time":231000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":233000,"text":"And some of these are actually meant"},{"time":235000,"text":"to mediate experiences."},{"time":237000,"text":"So the Discommunicator is a tool for arguments."},{"time":240000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":242000,"text":"And so actually it allows for an intense emotional exchange,"},{"time":245000,"text":"but is serves to absorb"},{"time":247000,"text":"the specificity of the words that are delivered."},{"time":250000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":256000,"text":"And in the end,"},{"time":258000,"text":"some of these things just act as invitations."},{"time":260000,"text":"So the Ear Bender literally puts something out there"},{"time":263000,"text":"so someone can grab your ear"},{"time":265000,"text":"and say what they have to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"So even though I'm really interested in the relationship"},{"time":269000,"text":"between people,"},{"time":271000,"text":"I also consider the ways"},{"time":273000,"text":"in which we relate to the world around us."},{"time":275000,"text":"And so when I was first living in New York City a few years back,"},{"time":278000,"text":"I was thinking a lot about"},{"time":280000,"text":"the familiar architectural forms that surrounded me"},{"time":282000,"text":"and how I would like to better relate to them."},{"time":285000,"text":"And I thought, \"Well, hey!"},{"time":287000,"text":"Maybe if I want to better relate to walls,"},{"time":289000,"text":"maybe I need to be more wall-like myself.\""},{"time":291000,"text":"So I made a wearable wall"},{"time":293000,"text":"that I could wear as a backpack."},{"time":295000,"text":"And so I would put it on"},{"time":297000,"text":"and sort of physically transform myself"},{"time":299000,"text":"so that I could either contribute to or critique"},{"time":301000,"text":"the spaces that surrounded me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"And so jumping off of that,"},{"time":308000,"text":"thinking beyond the built environment into the natural world,"},{"time":311000,"text":"I have this ongoing project called Botanicalls --"},{"time":314000,"text":"which actually enables houseplants"},{"time":316000,"text":"to tap into human communication protocols."},{"time":318000,"text":"So when a plant is thirsty,"},{"time":320000,"text":"it can actually make a phone call"},{"time":322000,"text":"or post a message to a service like Twitter."},{"time":325000,"text":"And so this really shifts the human/plant dynamic,"},{"time":329000,"text":"because a single house plant"},{"time":332000,"text":"can actually express its needs"},{"time":334000,"text":"to thousands of people at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337000,"text":"And so kind of thinking about scale,"},{"time":339000,"text":"my most recent obsession"},{"time":341000,"text":"is actually with glaciers -- of course."},{"time":345000,"text":"And so glaciers are these magnificent beings,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and there's lots of reasons to be obsessed with them,"},{"time":351000,"text":"but what I'm particularly interested in"},{"time":353000,"text":"is in human-glacier relations."},{"time":355000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":357000,"text":"Because there seems to be an issue."},{"time":359000,"text":"The glaciers are actually leaving us."},{"time":361000,"text":"They're both shrinking and retreating --"},{"time":363000,"text":"and some of them have disappeared altogether."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"And so I actually live in Canada now,"},{"time":368000,"text":"so I've been visiting one of my local glaciers."},{"time":370000,"text":"And this one's particularly interesting,"},{"time":372000,"text":"because, of all the glaciers in North America,"},{"time":374000,"text":"it receives the highest volume of human traffic in a year."},{"time":377000,"text":"They actually have these buses that drive up and over the lateral moraine"},{"time":380000,"text":"and drop people off on the surface of the glacier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"And this has really gotten me thinking"},{"time":385000,"text":"about this experience of the initial encounter."},{"time":387000,"text":"When I meet a glacier for the very first time,"},{"time":391000,"text":"what do I do?"},{"time":393000,"text":"There's no kind of social protocol for this."},{"time":397000,"text":"I really just don't even know"},{"time":399000,"text":"how to say hello."},{"time":401000,"text":"Do I carve a message in the snow?"},{"time":404000,"text":"Or perhaps I can assemble one"},{"time":406000,"text":"out of dot and dash ice cubes --"},{"time":408000,"text":"ice cube Morse code."},{"time":410000,"text":"Or perhaps I need to make myself a speaking tool,"},{"time":412000,"text":"like an icy megaphone"},{"time":414000,"text":"that I can use to amplify my voice"},{"time":416000,"text":"when I direct it at the ice."},{"time":418000,"text":"But really the most satisfying experience I've had"},{"time":420000,"text":"is the act of listening,"},{"time":422000,"text":"which is what we need in any good relationship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"And I was really struck by how much it affected me."},{"time":427000,"text":"This very basic shift in my physical orientation"},{"time":430000,"text":"helped me shift my perspective"},{"time":432000,"text":"in relation to the glacier."},{"time":434000,"text":"And so since we use devices"},{"time":436000,"text":"to figure out how to relate to the world these days,"},{"time":440000,"text":"I actually made a device called the Glacier Embracing Suit."},{"time":443000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":445000,"text":"And so this is constructed out of a heat reflected material"},{"time":448000,"text":"that serves to mediate the difference in temperature"},{"time":450000,"text":"between the human body and the glacial ice."},{"time":453000,"text":"And once again, it's this invitation"},{"time":456000,"text":"that asks people to lay down on the glacier"},{"time":460000,"text":"and give it a hug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"So, yea, this is actually just the beginning."},{"time":465000,"text":"These are initial musings for this project."},{"time":467000,"text":"And just as with the wall, how I wanted to be more wall-like,"},{"time":470000,"text":"with this project, I'd actually like to take more a of glacial pace."},{"time":474000,"text":"And so my intent"},{"time":476000,"text":"is to actually just take the next 10 years"},{"time":480000,"text":"and go on a series of collaborative projects"},{"time":484000,"text":"where I work with people from different disciplines --"},{"time":486000,"text":"artists, technologists, scientists --"},{"time":488000,"text":"to kind of work on this project"},{"time":490000,"text":"of how we can improve human-glacier relations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494000,"text":"So beyond that, in closing,"},{"time":497000,"text":"I'd just like to say that we're in this era"},{"time":500000,"text":"of communications and device proliferation,"},{"time":503000,"text":"and it's really tremendous and exciting and sexy,"},{"time":506000,"text":"but I think what's really important"},{"time":508000,"text":"is thinking about how we can simultaneously"},{"time":510000,"text":"maintain a sense of wonder and a sense of criticality"},{"time":513000,"text":"about the tools that we use and the ways in which we relate to the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}